{"questionId":"26770","questionHtml":"<p>Hence show that the snail reaches the point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>)</mo></math> before the water does.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p>time for water to reach top is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>10</mn></math> hours (seen anywhere)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong><br>OR</strong></p>\n<p>or at time <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>26</mn></math>, height of water is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>26</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>852</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong><br>THEN</strong></p>\n<p>so the water will not reach the snail&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"26770","referenceCode":"22M.1.AHL.TZ2.17b.ii","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Hence show that the snail reaches the point (10, 2) before the water does.","paper":"1","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"b.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","AHL 5.9—Differentiating standard functions and derivative rules","Topic 5—Calculus","AHL 5.13—Kinematic problems"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}